==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Astringe
<hw>As*tringe"</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧s*tr⟦icr⟧nj")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Astringed</conjf>
<pr>(-tr⟦icr⟧njd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Astringing</conjf> <pr>(-j⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>astringere</ets>; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>stringere</ets> to draw
tight. Cf. <er>Astrict</er>, and see <er>Strain</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bind fast; to constrict; to
contract; to cause parts to draw together; to compress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which contraction . . . <qex>astringeth</qex> the moisture of the
brain and thereby sendeth tears into the eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bind by moral or legal obligation.</def>
<rj><au>Wolsey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Astringency</ent>⟦br⟧
